72 68 :M
-.165(Multiple inheritance offset adjustments)A
58 92 :M
<A5>S
72 92 :M
-.189(Virtual function calls)A
23 116 :M
-.105(If a pointer to member\325s class does not use multiple inheritance,
some compilers assume there will be)A
23 128 :M
-.087(no offset adjustment.  This is a very small optimization; it usually
saves only one instruction.)A
23 152 :M
-.09(If a pointer to member\325s class does not contain or inherit virtual
functions, some compilers assume)A
23 164 :M
-.14(that a pointer to member dereference will never be a virtual function
call.  This is a noticeable)A
23 176 :M
