2.83 .283(Upcasting Across Virtual Inheritance)J
23 344 :M
f0_12 sf
-.088(These two issues intersect when we consider upcasting a pointer to
member beyond the class)A
23 356 :M
-.104(containing the original member, to a virtual base of that class.)A
23 380 :M
-.127(This is a problem because dereferencing the pointer to member would
require casting the object pointer)A
23 392 :M
-.081(down across virtual inheritance - which is a very expensive operation,
as it requires a dynamic cast.  It)A
23 404 :M
-.117(would be unreasonable to require an implicit dynamic cast in this
context.)A
23 428 :M
-.113(So there are two limitations on upcasting pointers to members:)A
58 452 :M
